<title>How to Use Claude =E2=80=94 Lead with Impact</title>

</head>
<body>
<div class=3D"page">

  <!-- HEADER -->
  <div class=3D"header">
    <div class=3D"header-left">
      <h1>How to Use <span>Claude</span></h1>
      <div class=3D"subtitle">A Practical Guide for Professionals</div>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"header-right">
      <div class=3D"logo-text">Lead with Impact</div>
      <div class=3D"logo-sub">leadwithimpact.io</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- COLUMN LABELS -->
  <div class=3D"col-labels">
    <div class=3D"col-label">Feature</div>
    <div class=3D"col-label">What It Does &amp; Try This First</div>
    <div class=3D"col-label">Pro Tip &nbsp;|&nbsp; Watch Out For</div>
  </div>

  <!-- ROW 1: CHAT -->
  <div class=3D"feature-row">
    <div class=3D"feature-label">
      <div class=3D"feature-icon">=F0=9F=92=AC</div>
      <div class=3D"feature-name">Chat</div>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"feature-main">
      <div class=3D"what-it-does">Where everyone starts. Where most people =
stop. Do not stop here =E2=80=94 Chat is the on-ramp, not the destination.<=
/div>
      <div class=3D"prompt-label">Try this first</div>
      <div class=3D"prompt-text">"Rewrite this email to sound confident and=
 professional =E2=80=94 clear, not cold."</div>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"feature-tips">
      <div class=3D"tip-block">
        <div class=3D"tip-label">Pro tip</div>
        <div class=3D"tip-text">Turn on Extended Thinking and Web Search be=
fore you start. Two clicks. Completely different results.</div>
      </div>
      <hr class=3D"tip-divider">
      <div class=3D"tip-block">
        <div class=3D"tip-label warning">Watch out for</div>
        <div class=3D"tip-text warning-text">Re-explaining who you are ever=
y single session. Set up a Project once and never do it again.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ROW 2: PROJECTS -->
  <div class=3D"feature-row">
    <div class=3D"feature-label">
      <div class=3D"feature-icon">=F0=9F=93=81</div>
      <div class=3D"feature-name">Projects</div>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"feature-main">
      <div class=3D"what-it-does">Your persistent workspace. Drop in your f=
iles, your role, your goals =E2=80=94 Claude remembers so you do not have t=
o repeat yourself.</div>
      <div class=3D"prompt-label">Try this first</div>
      <div class=3D"prompt-text">"Create a 'Workshop Facilitation' project.=
 Upload your bio, audience profile, and past session notes. Every output wi=
ll sound like you."</div>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"feature-tips">
      <div class=3D"tip-block">
        <div class=3D"tip-label">Pro tip</div>
        <div class=3D"tip-text">One Project per client, initiative, or topi=
c. Focused context produces sharper, more relevant outputs every time.</div=
>
      </div>
      <hr class=3D"tip-divider">
      <div class=3D"tip-block">
        <div class=3D"tip-label warning">Watch out for</div>
        <div class=3D"tip-text warning-text">Dumping every file you have in=
to one Project. Five well-chosen documents beat fifty scattered ones.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ROW 3: COWORK -->
  <div class=3D"feature-row">
    <div class=3D"feature-label">
      <div class=3D"feature-icon">=E2=9A=A1</div>
      <div class=3D"feature-name">Cowork</div>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"feature-main">
      <div class=3D"what-it-does">Claude stops answering and starts doing. =
Describe the outcome, step away, come back to finished work =E2=80=94 real =
files, in your folder.</div>
      <div class=3D"prompt-label">Try this first</div>
      <div class=3D"prompt-text">"Here is a folder of notes from my last th=
ree sessions. Organize them into a summary report with key themes and actio=
n items."</div>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"feature-tips">
      <div class=3D"tip-block">
        <div class=3D"tip-label">Pro tip</div>
        <div class=3D"tip-text">Set Global Instructions once =E2=80=94 your=
 name, your role, your preferred format. Every Cowork session starts alread=
y informed.</div>
      </div>
      <hr class=3D"tip-divider">
      <div class=3D"tip-block">
        <div class=3D"tip-label warning">Watch out for</div>
        <div class=3D"tip-text warning-text">Giving Claude a folder with no=
 context. Tell it the goal before it starts =E2=80=94 it plans better when =
it knows the destination.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ROW 4: CODE -->
  <div class=3D"feature-row">
    <div class=3D"feature-label">
      <div class=3D"feature-icon">=F0=9F=92=BB</div>
      <div class=3D"feature-name">Code</div>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"feature-main">
      <div class=3D"what-it-does">The developer powerhouse =E2=80=94 and th=
e engine Cowork is built on. Claude writes, debugs, and ships code directly=
. If you do not code, know it exists. If your team builds tools, share this=
 with them.</div>
      <div class=3D"prompt-label">Try this first</div>
      <div class=3D"prompt-text">"Ask your agency's developers if they are =
using Claude Code. If they are not, this is your conversation starter."</di=
v>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"feature-tips">
      <div class=3D"tip-block">
        <div class=3D"tip-label">Pro tip</div>
        <div class=3D"tip-text">Understanding Code explains why Cowork is s=
o capable. Same engine, friendlier interface. Knowing the connection makes =
you a smarter AI leader.</div>
      </div>
      <hr class=3D"tip-divider">
      <div class=3D"tip-block">
        <div class=3D"tip-label warning">Watch out for</div>
        <div class=3D"tip-text warning-text">Assuming Code is not relevant =
to you. If your organization builds or maintains any internal tools, someon=
e on your team needs to know this exists.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ROW 5: SKILLS -->
  <div class=3D"feature-row">
    <div class=3D"feature-label">
      <div class=3D"feature-icon">=F0=9F=8E=AF</div>
      <div class=3D"feature-name">Skills</div>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"feature-main">
      <div class=3D"what-it-does">Your personal Claude playbook. Build it o=
nce, use it forever. Claude learns your standards =E2=80=94 not just your p=
references.</div>
      <div class=3D"prompt-label">Try this first</div>
      <div class=3D"prompt-text">"Think of one task you do every week. Writ=
e down exactly how you want it done. That is your first Skill."</div>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"feature-tips">
      <div class=3D"tip-block">
        <div class=3D"tip-label">Pro tip</div>
        <div class=3D"tip-text">Build a Skill for every task you repeat wee=
kly =E2=80=94 workshop outlines, executive summaries, email formats. One go=
od Skill replaces an entire SOP.</div>
      </div>
      <hr class=3D"tip-divider">
      <div class=3D"tip-block">
        <div class=3D"tip-label warning">Watch out for</div>
        <div class=3D"tip-text warning-text">Confusing Skills with Projects=
. Projects hold your context. Skills teach Claude your process. You need bo=
th.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ROW 6: CONNECTORS -->
  <div class=3D"feature-row">
    <div class=3D"feature-label">
      <div class=3D"feature-icon">=F0=9F=94=97</div>
      <div class=3D"feature-name">Connectors</div>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"feature-main">
      <div class=3D"what-it-does">Claude inside the tools you already use. =
Google Drive, Slack, Notion, and 50+ more. Free to connect. No switching ta=
bs.</div>
      <div class=3D"prompt-label">Try this first</div>
      <div class=3D"prompt-text">"Find my most recent workshop outline in G=
oogle Drive and pull the key talking points."</div>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"feature-tips">
      <div class=3D"tip-block">
        <div class=3D"tip-label">Pro tip</div>
        <div class=3D"tip-text">Connectors work across Chat, Projects, and =
Cowork. Connect once =E2=80=94 Claude searches on demand across all three s=
urfaces.</div>
      </div>
      <hr class=3D"tip-divider">
      <div class=3D"tip-block">
        <div class=3D"tip-label warning">Watch out for</div>
        <div class=3D"tip-text warning-text">Thinking Connectors sync autom=
atically. Claude searches your tools when you ask =E2=80=94 not continuousl=
y in the background.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ROW 7: PLUGINS -->
  <div class=3D"feature-row">
    <div class=3D"feature-label">
      <div class=3D"feature-icon">=F0=9F=94=8C</div>
      <div class=3D"feature-name">Plugins</div>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"feature-main">
      <div class=3D"what-it-does">Pre-built power-ups for your role. Instal=
l one and Claude shows up as a specialist =E2=80=94 ready with the right co=
mmands for how you work.</div>
      <div class=3D"prompt-label">Try this first</div>
      <div class=3D"prompt-text">"Install a plugin for your field. Type / i=
n any chat to see every command available."</div>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"feature-tips">
      <div class=3D"tip-block">
        <div class=3D"tip-label">Pro tip</div>
        <div class=3D"tip-text">Start with two plugins that match your actu=
al job. Focused context outperforms having everything installed at once.</d=
iv>
      </div>
      <hr class=3D"tip-divider">
      <div class=3D"tip-block">
        <div class=3D"tip-label warning">Watch out for</div>
        <div class=3D"tip-text warning-text">Installing every plugin at onc=
e. Claude performs best with focused, relevant context =E2=80=94 not everyt=
hing at the same time.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ROW 8: SECURITY -->
  <div class=3D"feature-row security-row">
    <div class=3D"feature-label">
      <div class=3D"feature-icon">=F0=9F=94=92</div>
      <div class=3D"feature-name">Security First</div>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"feature-main">
      <div class=3D"what-it-does">Before anything else =E2=80=94 know what =
never goes in. AI tools are powerful. Protecting sensitive information is n=
on-negotiable.</div>
      <div class=3D"prompt-label">The rule</div>
      <div class=3D"prompt-text">"Would I post this publicly?" If no =E2=80=
=94 do not put it in AI. Use hypothetical scenarios and anonymized examples=
 instead.</div>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"feature-tips">
      <div class=3D"tip-block">
        <div class=3D"tip-label">Pro tip</div>
        <div class=3D"tip-text">Never input PII, personnel records, case nu=
mbers, or anything marked sensitive =E2=80=94 even in a "private" chat. Use=
 fictional stand-ins always.</div>
      </div>
      <hr class=3D"tip-divider">
      <div class=3D"tip-block">
        <div class=3D"tip-label warning">Watch out for</div>
        <div class=3D"tip-text warning-text">Assuming "private" means prote=
cted. Default to caution. Your judgment is the last line of defense =E2=80=
=94 not the platform.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- TAGLINE -->
  <div class=3D"tagline-bar">
    <p>"AI amplifies what already exists. My job is to make sure what exist=
s is worth amplifying."</p>
  </div>

  <!-- CTA STRIP -->
  <div class=3D"cta-strip">
    <div class=3D"cta-step"><div class=3D"num">1</div> Download the desktop=
 app at claude.com/download</div>
    <div class=3D"cta-arrow">=E2=86=92</div>
    <div class=3D"cta-step"><div class=3D"num">2</div> Get Pro ($20/mo)</di=
